
[1]suggestion

   SUGGES'TION, n. A hint; a first intimation, proposal or mention. The
   measure was adopted at the suggestion of an eminent philosopher.

   1. Presentation of an idea to the mind; as the suggestions of fancy or
   imagination; the suggestions of conscience.

   2. Insinuation; secret notification or incitement.

   3. In law, information without oath.
